column37:
1/ our number-one BIG problem is that absence of tracking and reporting PER FILE/FOLDER. This has us loose a considerable amount of time as we work with sometimes up to 5 or 6 bands : we create items (shirts, cd, LP) that we gather in "bands" files. This allow us a fast execution on the field. Yet, in the end, all the items appear in the reporting without any consideration of the file they're in, and we have to go manually through everything in order to know which band sold what, for what amount. And lemme tell you that when it comes to cash, it's not especially fun to have to open every single receipt, and write on paper whose band is getting the cash... All it would take to change, is the possibility to have the stats per FILE (items + card/cash) , in addition of the current reporting display. It would definitely make the life of merchandisers soooooooooo much easier, as we loose maybe 2 hours on these "unnecessary" operations on each assignment üôÇ

1bis / we'd prefer to bring Izettle with us abroad than SumUp, who works internationally. We had to buy their solution as we also travel to festivals. All our touring colleagues do the same. So, the possibility to use Izettle while on international tour would be truly beneficial. 

2/ we encountered many bugs while updating the list of the products "on the field", meaning during concert assignments : the registered items would suddenly disappear, or the folder they were in, having them all over. And this several times in the row, creating very challenging situations where we couldn't use the system to take paiements at all. üòü

3/ when working simultaneously with a colleague, an extremely delayed update with the new items, and often the disappearance of the folders they were in in the process of the update.

Feel free to contact us if there's any way for us to help develop the system further. üôÇ
